description.narrative: UNICEF has contributed to ensure that children under 5, pregnant and lactating women are able to access nutrition services of better quality with 3 main interventions: 1) prevention of severe acute malnutrition, 2) treatment for children dignosed with acute malnutrition both at health services and at community level and 3) strenghtening health services. Global Acute malnutrition has been addressed by implementing extensive deployment of nutritional screenings, covering small and remote states. UNICEF and partners strengthened the capacity of health services on nutrition interventions to prevent undernutrition through strenghthening staff skills as well as providing supplies for adequate nutrition care. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
